text: in C:   #include <stdio.h> #include <stdlib.h>  int get_prime(int n, int *x){  int i = 1;  int j = 1;    while(j <= n){   if(x[i] == 1){    j++;   }   i++;  }    return i - 1; }  int main(){  int j;  int n = 10000;  int code[] = {1206, 301, 384, 5};  int key[] = {1, 1, 2, 2};  int ISBN;    //sieve  int x[10000] = {[0 ... 9999] = 1};    x[1] = 0;   for(int i = 2; i < sizeof(x)/sizeof(int)/2; i++){   j = 2*i;   while(j < n){    x[j] = 0;    j += i;   }  }    printf("ISBN = ");    for(int i = 0; i < sizeof(code)/sizeof(int); i++){   ISBN = get_prime(code[i], x) - key[i];   printf("%d", ISBN);  }    printf("\n");   return 0; }
